t-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>, from the Middle English personal name <i>Bete</i>, a pet form of <i>Betris</i> (see   Beatrice  ). In East Anglia, however, where the name is concentrated, it is of Dutch origin (see 1 above), as evidenced by the census of 1881. This surname is now rare in Britain.","Probably an altered form of German   Beetz  ."]},{"name":"Baeten","meanings":["Dutch: metronymic from a short form of the female personal name<i>Beatrix</i> (see   Beatrice  )."]},{"name":"Beat","meanings":["Scottish (Angus) and English: variant of <b>Beet</b>, from the Middle English personal name <i>Bete</i>, a pet form of <i>Betris</i> (see   Beatrice  ). Compare   Beets  ."]},{"name":"Beeton","meanings":["English (Cambridgeshire and Suffolk): from the Middle English personal name <i>Beton</i> (a diminutive of <i>Bete</i>, a pet form of   Beatrice  ), or a variant of   Beaton  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Beatrice was born about 1220. She married Robert de Hougham about 1268. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1271, at the age of 52."},"et":{"abt 1220–1271":"umbes 1220–1271","1212–1273":"1212–1273","1240–1301":"1240–1301","1242–Male":"1242–Surnud","1244–1340":"1244–1340","1220–1271":"1220–1271","ABT 1242":"umbes 1242","1301":"1301","1212":"1212","1244":"1244","ABT 1268":"umbes 1268","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1340":"1340","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","abt 1220":"umbes 1220","1271":"1271","Wavering,Kent,Eng":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Bishopsbourne, Kent, Eng":"Bishopsbourne, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1220–1271":"noin 1220–1271","1212–1273":"1212–1273","1240–1301":"1240–1301","1242–Male":"1242–Kuollut","1244–1340":"1244–1340","1220–1271":"1220–1271","ABT 1242":"noin 1242","1301":"1301","1212":"1212","1244":"1244","ABT 1268":"noin 1268","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1340":"1340","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","abt 1220":"noin 1220","1271":"1271","Wavering,Kent,Eng":"Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Bish